    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix UE ID reset issue causing port conflicts in NAS user API initialization\n\n### Summary\nIn the NAS UE task initialization, when running in standalone mode, the UE ID was being incorrectly reset to 0 after all initialization was completed. This caused all UEs to attempt to use the same port (base_port + 0) when establishing their user API connections, leading to port conflicts and initialization failures.\n\nThe issue was reproduced by running multiple UEs in standalone mode and observing that only the first UE could successfully initialize its user API connection, while subsequent UEs failed with port binding errors.\n\nThis fix removes the erroneous UE ID reset, ensuring each UE maintains its correct ID throughout the initialization process and gets assigned a unique port number.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/nas_ue_task.c`: Removed the line that was resetting `user->ueid = 0` in the standalone mode initialization path (line 177).\n"
}